SEMINARS ON TEACHING
<paragraph><sentence>The six seminars below count toward the Documentation of Teaching
Development Program</sentence>.  </paragraph>

Overview of Student Motivation
	Wednesday, May 24, <stime>2:00</stime> - <etime>4:00 PM</etime>, <location>Carnegie Conference Room, Warner Hall</location> 
<paragraph><sentence>Instructors often take for granted that our students have the motivation
to learn what we teach,  but the level or type of motivation varies
greatly with different courses, assignments and students</sentence>.  <sentence>This seminar
will provide a framework of theories of motivation and provide
opportunities to discuss how instructors can engage students more fully 
in learning in their courses</sentence>.  </paragraph>
